<p><br />The Gateway Foundations Seminar "Academic Planning &amp; Advising" introduces students to the requirements and resources that will help them in planning their academic path at BYU-Idaho and in progressing towards graduation successfully and efficiently. This seminar focuses on important academic advising information that will save students time, money, and future problems. If you would like to help students avoid the pitfalls of poor academic planning, consider becoming a peer facilitator for this seminar.</p>
<h2>Qualifications</h2>
<ul>
<li>Have the ability to present information in a clear and professional way</li>
<li>Complete at least two semesters at BYU-Idaho prior to becoming a peer facilitator</li>
<li>Have a minimum GPA of 2.8</li>
<li>Live the BYU-Idaho Honor Code and Dress and Grooming Standards</li>
<li>No current violations with the Dean of Students office<br /><br /></li>
</ul>
<h2><a href="https://cms.byui.edu/emp/sites/crawfordv/Lists/Academic%20Planning%20Facilitator%20Application/Item/newifs.aspx?List=ef18d1e0%2D0286%2D45a8%2Da8f1%2D919a1f793eba&amp;isdlg=1">Apply Here</a></h2>
<p><br />For questions, email: <a href="mailto:gatewayseminars@byui.edu">gatewayseminars@byui.edu</a></p>
